      "review_summary": "The PR adds a channel setup hook that lets Feishu reinterpret explicit `--bind` values with `oc_`/`ou_` prefixes as route peers and wires that hook into agent binding parsing and generation.\n\nPR surface: Source +58. Total +58 across 3 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level: current main parses `feishu:oc_test` as `match.accountId`, while Feishu inbound routing supplies `peer` and the route resolver prioritizes peer bindings. I did not run a live Feishu message route in this read-only review.",
